content: I have a free app (my calendar) and it works better than this. I'm going to use that one instead again. I used it for years with no problems and have been struggling with this one for some time. It feels like a scam, though I'd hate to even think that.

This app had a lot of potential, but a lack of updates has rendered it unusable. I love the concept behind this app and the nutritional suggestions based off of symptoms, but lately I can't even open the app without it freezing.
Love this app. The only suggestion I would make is to have the option to be able to add when things are going well and not just symptoms. For example: feeling productive, excited, rested, calm
A great app full of womb wisdom. It would be great if the app told you what day(the number)of your cycle you are on.
Save your money
I love the idea of this app but the technical issues are extremely frustrating.

Terrible app. Constantly crashes (as in, won't allow you to upload any symptoms from the day before, if you forgot) so that you need to constantly delete and reinstall it. This time, even reinstalling 5 times hasn't helped, it's now totally not working, and the "support" team say there's nothing they can do. for a paid app this is really unacceptable.

Too bad there have been no updates or fixes in over 2 years despite the many complaints and comments. Could be a great app if I didn't have to re-install at least once a month due to freezing. Also saw some great feedback a while ago about adding more symptoms but that has not been done. Please fix this. Thank you.
This app stopped working some 3 months in. No matter how many times I've asked for assistance, I haven't gotten any.
Just installed and it's glitching and crashing before I have entered much data. Not ideal for a paid app when there are free ones which function well.
Constantly crashes and just wants to sell you their suppliments

I really wish this app would work properly. I have uninsty and reinstalled this app several times. There is always a glitch. You are not able to edit past periods. This issue has been going on for several years and I am disappointed it has never been fixed
I bought and paid for the app and when I install it asks me again to pay.

I keep wondering why I bought this app. It does not work after about a month of using. It will not allow me to track my flo...which is the entire point of the app. Disappointed because if this app worked it would be such a useful tool!
It worked for 2months and then stopped. Can't even update the day symptoms.I like the idea and the theory is great just I won't recommend the app
The app use to be good but its not anymore. The calendar is confusing to read and the app takes a long time to open every time because its loading. Please update the app and fix these issues.

The interface is easy to use and nice aesthetically. However, there seems to always be some sort of glitch when entering in data. Some days it works, some times for a week or more it doesn't, which is very frustrating when you are trying to understand your hormones.

I love the design of the app, the advice and all info given are great. However there are always some technical issues. Most of the time the app does not function and I cannot enter a day to record my cycle... I attempted to uninstall and reinstall again but nope still not working. Such a shame because I believe this is a great app, but for a paid one, these problems should be fixed...
It crashes and you can adjust your cycle. The app needs a overhaul. At this point it's a waste of money.

I don't know what I would do without it... It literally has anything and everything you possibly need to do or know to regulate your cycles, to get pregnant (either naturally or IVF), or to better manage your perimenopause... Even though I am 45 I'm going through all of these things all at once. A woman is never simply "simple." And this app keeps up! I cannot tell you the relief and ease of mind this app provides on a daily basis üôèüïâÔ∏è

Dear Alisa and the developers, For a paid app, this one is doing a bad job. I appreciate the fact that you went into depths, to create the Womancode and Flo protocol, and to incorporate into an app. But the app crashes and asks for update every single time it opens. It takes ages to load and is irritating to use because of that. We, as the woman community, wants to have better life and I am sure you know that is why we use this app. Please fix this.

I'm sad, it's so good for giving advice and learning about the phases and how to adjust your life accordingly. I'm totally into that. However, it does not adjust to my cycle length over time. It says 27 days and I'm an average 31. So its WAY off. This is the foremost reason why I wanted a period tracking app. I just contacted help for the 3rd time. Then read the reviews here and understand I'm not the first one. I'll hope for a fix or a better app in my future.
Please make this app work. Thanks
Love the app, when it's working. Going through a really buggy phase right now, I presume.

It doesn't work, plain and simple. I wish I read the reviews closer before handing over my $ for nothing... How is this even allowed? I can't enter information, I emailed support for help and they suggested some options that did not fix the problem and then didn't reply when I asked for further assistance. Really really terrible and disappointing for something I was really excited about.
It worked for a month and now I can no longer track my symptoms. Plus the solutions to symptoms are based on their plans that you need to buy. Switching apps to something more reliable.
Brilliant! Women need to know these cycles!

This app is a great tool to use in addition to Alisa's books. You plug in your symptoms and it tells you which foods to eat and which exercises to do during each phase of your cycle. A very helpful reference tool if you don't have her book handy!

It is fantastic for people that already know physiology and anatomy basics but could use a bit more information regarding nutrition, more of the specific examples like what types of food contain the things that the app recommends in your diet.

I struggle with this app every time I try to use it. I can never add details and as a result it thinks my cycle is 80-120 days long... not the case, I have 27 day cycle. I have reached out and am told to uninstall and reinstall or that my phone may be too old for the software. At any rate I just wish it would work for me.

Great concept, poor execution. I want to love this app because I believe in it's intention. The cycle/lifestyle suggestions and information is useful but the period tracking is pretty much useless. It doesn't adapt based on your actual cycle history so the predictions are basically inaccurate every month - that is when the app isn't crashing and you can actually open it to enter data.
It worked fine untril couple a days ago ehan it froze and I can't put in my symptoms. Please fix it!
I loved the app for the first month and a half but then it just stopped working. Im no longer able to enter my daily symptoms.
Too many bugs that make it unusable. Don't bother. It's just another way for Alisa to sell her other products. Hasn't been updated in 2 years.
Always glitchy but when I got my new phone finding my account is impossible. Had to reach out to customer support, hopefully they can help.

Not user friendly. My cycle is irregular and it didn't allow for changing of period end days. Also, it is a paid app (a friend recommended), yet the app spams you with their expensive add on "programs". I have some found several free apps that unlike much better.

I have had this app for about 4 months and it was so good at helping me track my cycle and understand what my symptoms are suggesting during my cycle. The advice it used to give about what foods are good to eat during specific times of my cycle was so helpful. But a few months on and I can no longer put my data in to track my symptoms. Really frustrating and disappointing. Seems like there is an error once you have used it for a certain amount of time. Not designed very well.
Disappointing. If you are ever late or early on your period it throws the entire thing out. The app can't re-sync the dates. Absolutely pointless.

I loved it until I didn't. The first month or two, it worked great. After that, it stopped letting me track my symptoms and make notes unless I was in my menstrual phase. So frustrating. I hope the bugs for this get fixed for Android users.
I like this app so far but wish the presumption in terms of partners was not hetronormative. It is a bit exclusionary to assume all women using the app will have a male partner.

Been glitch from the start about a year ago and it just keeps getting worse. Too many bugs to call them features. The FREE app I've been using for a few years can track more and has never had a glitch. Apparently from other reviews this has been going on for ages - why aren't Flo fuxing it?!
Thank you so much vitti!

Love the features, has great information in the app, easy to track. However, I constantly have problems with the app, it will stop working multiple times a week and I end up having to clear my data or sometimes I just stop using it for awhile.

I really loved the app for the first month. Then it stopped allowing me to log symptoms, something I have seen happen commonly from other reviews. I contacted flo living via their webpage with my issue and there was no response. Really disappointed I paid for the app. There are similar apps for free
App is awful and doesn't work most of the time. Waste of my time and money.

All of a sudden it stopped working.... I am no longer able to add updates on the current date nor days that have passed unless it's about a month ago. It's very odd. It will tell me the phase that I'm in and the recommendations but I think it's useful that I add information and it just won't let me.

Such a cool app for tracking your period but also amazing insight into what foods /exercise/ mindset you're in in your different hormonal phases which helps you optimise for each phase. I've been following this for a few months and cannot recommend it more!

Decent app for tracking menstrual days. I wish it had more variety of symptoms available. And even more than that, some of the "symptoms" should be more than a [yes/no] type option. For example: spotting, it would be more beneficial to be able to record and track color and texture. For a paid app, it should be a lot more flexible and detail oriented. The recommendations offered to eliminate symptoms are awesome, and the suggestions are interesting. I really like this part.
This is a great app. I can't wait to see it evolve with Alisa Vitti and all the approaches to living in the Flo!
Not intuitive, difficult to use and suddenly stopped letting me track anything.

Unfortunately the app is basically unusable. It worked okay for a month or two but now I cannot enter or track anything. I have reinstalled it many different times and it has not started working again. I love Alisa but she needs to hire someone to revamp this app, I believe it's detrimental to her brand in its current state.

App is very glitchy. I spend a lot of time waiting for it to start up, most of the time I have to close and restart it 3 times before it works. It is very difficult to make adjustments to your cycle in the app. The theory is great, the app doesn't live up to it. I have other free period tracking apps that actually work. Very disappointing for a paid app.

Disappointing! Alisa's book is great but this app doesn't hit the mark at all. Not user friendly, layout is visualy hard to follow and it's slow. I'm sticking to my free but reliable and user friendly original period tracker app I have been using for years as you can back up your data if lost - unfortunately also not possible with this app!

Such an amazing app unfortunately the tech side needs improvements. I paid for the app and it worked great for about 5 months my naturopath and I were using the data from it and the tracking to customize my plan. But now I can only see the calender I can't add symptoms or look on past symptoms. I really hope Alissa invests some time into improving this. I've tried uninstalling and reinstalling and no luck.

It doesn't work. I wanted to love this app. But it's a joke for a paid app. I have to reinstall it constantly and the add symptoms button doesn't work forcing me to have to reinstall again. It's infuriating. I've read other reviews having the same problem and customer support recommended reinstalling. Over and over. That is ridiculous. This app is garbage. The content is great and I love the books but this app has too many bugs. Alissa needs to have it redesigned this is ruining her brand.

I love the app when it works but it constantly crashes upon opening. As someone with irregular periods who really counts on a reliable period tracker, I unfortunately have to switch back to using another one that doesn't crash.

This isn't a great tracker for your cycle. The tips are good, but if you want any real value, you have to pay for it. Also, when I toggle between tabs, it take a while to load. I wish I hadn't paid for this because I have better free apps.
Highly recommended to me. I won't be repeating that recommendation. Worked fine on my Samsung for a couple months, but now glitches and won't let me input any information. A waste of money and space.
Great concept, terrible app. Freezes constantly. Can't schedule new periods. Worst app I have ever paid for.

Really dissapointed. I've been following the creator of thos app for a while and I have really wanted to learn more about my cycle and the cycle syncing method. At first all was great and then it started glitching. I can't add any symptoms. As another user stated it's just a glorified calendar. You can just google all the informatiom when it comes to knowing the 4 phases of your cycle and what to do/eat during each one. Thankfully I kept my other app while trying this out.

I like this app enough to continue using it, but not enough that I don't keep another period app on my phone. It glitches alot, and I don't like how the app expects that my menstrual phase will be the same # of days every month. Sometimes it last 3/4 days, sometimes 7. The lifestyle and diet tips are cool and helpful. The heteronormative language is not.

Completely useless on an Android moto7. I paid the $2 for the app and have never been able to successfully open it on this phone. When I had an iPhone I was able to use it. Now it literally will crash within seconds of opening the app. I don't have this issue with any other app. I'm disappointed because it could have been useful when TTC.
Great when it worked, now it just crashes

I wanted to love this app so badly! I highly rate Alicia Vitti and the work she does, however this app is super glitchy, it loses my data all the time, and is not useful for me. I'm only giving it two stars based on Alicia's reputation as a kick-ass woman doing amazing work (otherwise it would be one star).

MyFLO gives you useful insight into where you are in your cycle, why you might be experiencing certain symptoms and what you can do to feel your best during each phase of your cycle. It is unlike anything I have ever used and has been an important tool in gaining awareness around my cycle, as well as improving awful PMS symptoms.
It stopped working -unable to add daily symptoms as template not loading
love it
It started off great, I'm really excited about Alisa's work. But the app stopped allowing me to track my symptoms after just a couple of weeks I was using it! Hope they will fix this!

Started off great. Really liked the suggestions for what to do in the phase of my cycle. Appreciated the ability to track my symptoms. It's not the most visually stunning app but it works! Until it didn't work. After my first period the ability to track my symptoms no longer works (or works intermittently). Really frustrating. Now it's just a glorified calendar.

I can't believe I paid for this app! It gives you very few tips to work on your cycle, the range of symptoms is limited and it stops working every time I add one day. I have to uninstall it and reinstall it every day or every time I want to add something. As said by many people, don't waste you money on this app!
Great concept but so many bugs
Cant click "sync my partner" on my samsung galaxay tab a even after update. All the other buttons work. Except this majn button I'm using this app for! Please fix or tell me a work around.
This app stopped working after two cycles. I couldn't input new info or look back on previous symptoms. Really disappointing.

I love this app. Although I do wish it had more symptoms to check off and I wish you could rate your symptoms based on intensity. Like, I might want to mark off "anxiety" as a symptom one day but only as like a 3/10, but then maybe a 8/10 a different day. It would be helpful to track the intensity of my symptoms as it's rarely a black-and-white thing.
Great!

There are much, much better free period tracking apps out there. Seriously! Even the one that comes as part of your fitness tracker will be better than this! There are only a limited symptoms and it's essentially a platform to promote the extortionately priced add on programmes it suggests for you symptoms. Also, lo! And behold 3 weeks in and Im having the same problems logging any symptoms as everyone else is who hates the app is having. Don't waste you time and money on this app

Great concept, poor execution. really bugs me that it constantly tells me I'm in the wrong part of my cycle. I'm trying to make my cycle longer, you keep telling me days before I'm menstruating that I'm in my menstrual phase, which is telling my subconscious brain to hurry up and be in that phase already! It's the opposite of helpful which is why I bought the app in the first place. Please help as I'm uninstalling
I really have been looking forward to this app, but its not letting me track everyday, it now doesn't let me re install as directed by support, doesn't even work

The app worked fine for the first few weeks but after that it wouldn't let me track my symptoms. I had to uninstall and reinstall it almost daily. The app is also really bare bones and even though you pay for the app, they want to upsell you for all of the features outside of just tracking symptoms.
I love that this app explains each week but sometimes the app just doesn't work. You can't always add in info

The app has long lags and freezes. I'm often unable to enter data and the calendar scrolling makes it difficult to see which month I'm looking at. Also doesn't have a great way to track mood and emotional health.

It started out as a great app but I can't tap to bring up the daily symptom etc. Page anymore, maybe a bug that needs to be fixed? Update, will now not open üò≠ 2nd update, Uninstalled and reinstalled and working like normal, am worried it might not last, it did keep all my entries and information though!
The app was not user friendly. I removed from my phone.

It's a great idea with many useful options (symptom specific suggestions, sync partner). However, the app has serious conceptual and technical issues. There is no option for back up or email your data. This alone is a scandal. All your data is lost if something happens, and you cannot export and crunch your symptoms and data in any way. This app is SLOW. Slow to load, slow to process a new period. It's visually ugly, doesn't count days (?!?), weeks only start on Sunday. For a paid app - not ok!
The app refuses to open at all after I've only had it for about 2 weeks. Cleared cache, stopped the app, restarted the phone. This is the 3rd day in a row it won't open.

UPDATE: It no longer opens the current day I'm trying to edit. So Frustrating üòí I want to like this app, but, it continually stops, constantly checks for updates, is really slow, tells me my cycle is too short regardless of how many days (my cycle fits into a regular length cycle), freezes all the time, and I've uninstalled it and reinstalled it numerous times, and still it continually doesn't work. I love the idea of it and keeping track of everything, but pen & paper doesn't shutdown

I love the app but it needs an update. It refuses to open and when it does (which is rarely) it takes time to load or refused to let me log data. I do find it somewhat helpful when it works but the information is repetitive, no additional information
I can't input data any more
It keeps shutting off. I'm gonna give it another try by reinstalling it, hopefully it'll open and won't waste my time

If the app finally DOES load after an unreasonably long amount of time, it won't let me input data on today's date. It always lags, crashes or something else so it is too frustrating for me to log ANYTHING if I finally manage to get it to work. I love the concept of the app and the helpful tips for different phases of my cycle, but it only works every 11th time. I've reached out to customer service several times to no avail, so I'm going back to Clue.

Needs updates but I'm hanging on. I've been using it a couple years. I love the info it provides but it needs improvement in layout and features. It was confusing to find where to edit cycle dates. Months on the calendar view need to be more clearly defined, it just looks like all days of the year listed in a long scrolling screen with months indicated by tiny font. A widget with countdown would be great.

Stopped Letting Me Update (Android, Samsung Galaxy s7) I got this app 1.5 months ago after purchasing In the Flo, which is a great book!, and wanted to try this app out in addition. I am giving 2 stars because I love how it was working before, and the insights it had but now it won't let me add notes. Other issues: -slow open -"schedule it" not linking up with calendar -sometimes difficult to edit previous comments (have to X out and reopen to edit) I like this app, please fix it.

Long time Clue user but I read the book and gave this a try for $2.99. Holy Mother of Advertising Batman! Guess what I dont want to buy again? Your book! Confusing to use with a complicated layout and pop-ups galore. The pink color scheme... I woke up in a puddle of my own blood I don't need to be reminded that I'm a woman. There is a partner tab... maybe I have 5 sexual partners. What was I hoping for? Just some diet reminders at appropriate times. Uninstalling this app and going back to Clue.

Overall I love the app!! But It is a little annoying that on the calendar view it defaults to the date I started using it. It would also be nice if it listed more food recommendations. The audio book came with a nice chart of what foods to eat during what phase. It's a pain to find the printout, that should be in the app. Otherwise great app! Love the symptom specific advice.
This app is great when it works. Sadly, it never works.
Its not working! I changed phone and it didn't transfer my data and now doesn't even let me to add my new periods!! What's going on? It used to be a great app!
I love the idea of this app but I'm having the same problems as everyone else. It worked for a few weeks and now I haven't been able to entire data for a week.
Has potential but crashes Regularly

So far I really like the app. I've been using it for a little over a month to try to track my cycle (irregular due to breastfeeding) so far my biggest issue is the "getting to know you" questions it asks when you log symptoms. It asks the same ones over and over (if I had kids, or if I used birth control 2-3 each) or redundant ones (yesterday if I was married, and today if I was single?) so I know that it's not using them for anything. I wish it actually used your response to help understand you

Great app, but stopped working after about a month. I would expect an app I have to pay for wouldn't crash this way, but here we are. Edit: even when I try to reset my password to log back in the link is broken. Do not even waste your time.
This app constantly freezes. I'm very disappointed.

Not the best app. Great info, but very confusing to use and stopped working even after I uninstalled and reinstalled it.it will no longer load when I try to log symptoms. basically all it is trying to do is get you to by the $300 way over priced personal help. The book is great, app is a great idea, but price is way too much. One of the first apps I have ever paid for and will make me rethink in the future. Now i am trying to install on my new phone and it is asking me to pay for the app agaim
Great information and helpful to understand my mood and gives insight into activity for each day of cycles! However, the app keeps glitching and freezing and takes a long time to open

Worked well for a few months, then nothing! App crashes after a few seconds or never opens at all. When I have reached out to address the crashing app I'm told to uninstall then reinstall for the update which worked the first time, but never again. Final straw today at the doc, open the app to discover a year worth of info just GONE. If i could rate 0 stars I would. Maintain your app ffs!

Unfortunately this app keeps crashing, if it opens at all in the first place. Shame, cause it's a great concept and is even more useful to those of us following the flo lifestyle designed by Alisa Vitti herself. Hope the bugs get fixed and I can come back to using this app in the future...

Basically just a promotion for other more expensive products that she offers and I was stupid enough to pay to download it Nothing more than a calendar tracker of sorts that you can use Google calendar for

With MyFlo I always know where I am in my cycle. I sort of rely on the app now and regularly check the pages giving intel and tips on what best to eat and what to do at work and socially each phase. Although I had some technical issues (after a month, the app wouldn't open up the input window no matter where I clicked), customer service helped me through it.

This app sucks, I feel swindled by Alisa Vitti. she cares so little about her app that she can't be bothered to fix the fact that its perpetually frozen & you cant log anything no matter how many times you close & reopen or uninstall & redownload. She claims to want to help ppl recognize & correct their imbalances but can't provide a legitimate platform to do it. Your better off writing it on a stone tablet then on this stupid app. Read all her books & still think the app is a WASTE OF MONEY!
This app doesn't work! I barely used it and it kept stopping even I did not open it! Really poorly executed! Not worth the money

I loved this app, and it was giving me real insights in what was happening inside my body at the different times throughout my cycle. And then it stopped working. Should have read the comments before purchasing the app. I guess she is just doing it for the money?!?? If this has been going on for so long, how come it has not been fixed?!? Just saying...
The app has a lot of good information but is very glitchy, stops working, or stops saving your data.
This app needs an update. After only one month of using it, it doesn't work anymore. Very disappointed
Just stopped working and letting me log things.

Great info but has a glitch that affects my whole ability to really track my cycle. The schedule a new period button doesn't work and I've uninstalled it and reinstalled it, it worked once and then stopped again.
Stopped working üòë

This app cannot sync with my cycle like it's supposed to. I cannot change the days like I am already in luteal phase but the app is still in ovulation phase and I cannot change it. I would install it again if they fix this app.
App stopped working 1 month in

Officially totally stopped working on my phone! I thought if I left it open to load for a while or uninstalled it again, it would eventually start working but it's completely stopped lol. I loved this app when it worked (which was only half a cycle)! Why don't they fix it?! Guess I'll have to find a different app with less information. People should start leaving their recommendations here.
finding it very difficult to navigate, not very helpful, incorrect and frustrating. the book might be a better idea until they decide to improve this app which I hope they do
Completely stopped working after a few weeks since buying the app :( I really had high hopes for it, because what I did get to experience for the time it was working, was actually helpful.

Always crashing! I love the idea of this app and its great tips, moon/cycle stages; along with the ability to log symptoms and make notes. However, the constant crashing and slow response of the app, spoils the experience for me. Feeling I'll need to install a different one.....üòîüòå

This app is a great concept but stopped letting me input symptoms by the second cycle. It crashes constantly as well. Also wish you could keep a food journal, input your own symptoms that aren't listed, and indicate if you exercised, if you are sick, etc. It falls a little short and feels incomplete. Not worth buying just yet.

Amazing concept. Very poor execution, I can see that people reviewing had the same experience, so there's got to be something specific that's wrong with the app. It works for a couple of cycles and then either shuts down when I try to load it or just doesn't respond or shows that my period lasted 10 days... Just doesn't work like it's means to
This does not work well. The app stopped working so I can't input any information.

Serious issues with syncing and loading. Somehow the ads (barely disguised as announcements that a new book/product has been released) seem to load fine, but the app only loads sometimes. Tech support is responsive, but only seems able to recommend uninstalling and reinstalling. No way I want to uninstall and reinstall a misbehaving app at least once a month (usually more). Things don't completely sync, so that eventually at times I end up with a message saying I'm entering the menstrual phase when it just ended several days ago (hasn't synced with MY information, instead is basing things on the generic information, even though I've checked multiple times that I have it set to base on MY information). No ability to turn off push notifications, which also aren't actually synced with my individual information. Absolutely not worth the purchase, which is so sad because the product itself COULD be amazing.
Started off great, but after a few weeks stopped working... it won't let me enter daily symptoms anymore. What a huge disappointment, especially because this is an app you have to pay for.
Great info, terrible app. I have literally been waiting years for them to fix the issues that everyone complains about and they never do. Not worth the money for the frustration.
Was good at first, but now I can't enter symptoms from past days. Nothing happens when I select the date.

Great content, but stopped working. I had high hopes for this app after listening to Alisa Vitti on a couple of podcasts, and was really looking forward to embracing her approach. However, sadly after 11 days the app stopped working and will no longer let me add my symptoms. So disappointing as there is some great information on there. Real shame! I'm now using Flo instead as a friend recommended it, which is very good and still working!!

Do Not Purchase! I recorded my data for a month & then it deleted for my visablility when I got a new phone. I contacted customer service had a back & forth for over a week! And they said they could see my data on their end but could not send it to me (so I can at the very least enter it into a new app) or fix the problem as to why it wasn't visable! They also have NOT provided a refund. This is a Major disappointment. every symptom I enter Im prompted to buy a $500 meal plan, hormone plan etc

I've been using this app for less than one month, started out well with some really useful info and tips. But now that's stopped, can't input any data at all. Waste of time, so unfortunate. Not even a whole month!
Downloaded app. It worked for two days, then has been spinning ever since, and has never opened again.

Excellent the few days it works, then it totally stops, blacks out, looses important info... I have restarted again & again & it is SO stressful when I enjoy it a few days & then can't enter any more information. App keeps stopping or freezing. I use GLOW app now which works 99% of time. I liked using both due to the phases info from MyFLO but I guess I will just upgrade GLOW.

Great concept and it started off fine. But now it rarely let's me enter my daily symptoms. Its telling me my period is 13 days late, but I have entered my last on time period and its symptoms. In fact a lot of the time the app won't open. It just doesn't function as it should for an app I paid for. The only reason I still have it installed is because I like to refer back to its previous recommendations. It would also be nice if it considered other info such as whether I've exercised or am sick.

love content, but it's SO slow! Edit: I have tried downloading this app multiple times hoping the kinks have been worked out of it, but every time it freezes up my phone and is so tedious to use. So disappointed as it would be great if it worked!
Not worth paying for, app crashes all the time. Better off using free apps. Very disappointing ‚òπÔ∏è
I like the features and bits of information, but it won't let me add a new period. It thinks my cycles are 157 days long and the information provided is then inaccurate.

This app is disappointing. There are constant pop ups and push notifications about buying more products from the company. Not a lot of helpful information for $2, should be free. Also it checks for updates before opening so if you don't have a connection it won't even open.
Fantastic app. Helps you be more active with your cycle and managing symptoms. Helpful tips.

The apps works great for a couple of cycles and then eventually just stops functioning entirely, not allowing me to input new data as symptoms occur. I've had to completely clear and reenter my previous cycle information a couple times now just to get it working again for a while. At this point, I'm looking at other apps to try. content: Life changing but needs to fix a crashing issue. This app is a companion to the book Womancode by Alisa Vitti and I have used it for six months to chart my cycle and steps I take to improve my health. I've never stuck to a program that long and without the app I never would have stuck to it using the book alone. Ive reduced symptoms, lost weight, almost eliminated sugar cravings, and gained more energy. One thing I do wish is that the app made it clear you need to read the book first to get all the background info, then use the app to track how you apply it. From a technical standpoint, it worked better on my iPhone, but when I switched to Android in December it began to crash a lot more and often not open at all. I recently reinstalled it and it's doing a bit better. I'm sincerely hoping I can keep using it bc it is an incredible accountability tool.

This Is a handy app as far as tracking my cycle and getting recommendations based on my symptoms goes. Unfortunately, it's very cis-normative and heteronormative. Some people who menstruate are queer, non-binary, trans. It refers to boyfriends and asks questions applicable to straight couples only. Making a more gender neutral version with more colour variation and better representation of the wide spectrum of people that experience menstruation would make this app more accessible.
It often has glitches.
It crashes too much,  and takes like 5 minutes to open or doesn't open at all. Very frustrating!

In the meantime I suggest just doing research on your own about menstruation phases and recommended lifestyle changes for each phase. Figure out how long your phases are by number of days, then use a different period tracker.

So glitchy. Used to work fine, but now Cervical Fluid information always disappears. Sucks because that was the main reason I spent money on this app üòí

I love this app! I have started learning more about my cycle in the past year and this is the first app I felt was worth my time. Other apps, it's like you are just adding stuff for no reason. Here I get clear ideas on what I could improve. Also, it's the only app I know which tracks all four phases of your cycle and I love knowing where I am each day. It's a restaurant and I plan to go deeper with womancode and maybe one of the programs in the future. I have recommended this app to all my girlfriends.

Other than having issues getting it to open lately(doesn't respond when trying to open at times and force closes occasionally), this app is great! I still use Fertility Friend as my backup, especially since I can't count on this one to open when I need it to all of the time & I have a horrible memory. Love the tips and diet suggestions!

Tried it again after a few months. Hoping for better results. Still disapointed. Calendar operations are awful! Reverted back to my freebee app in days. Also uses data every time I open it. Un installing after this review, AGAIN

This app does not count my actual period days as part of my cycle and keeps telling me that my cycle is too short, but if it counted all the days including my period then I'm exactly the 28 day cycle I'm supposed to be having. Annoying, but some of the other suggestions about cycle synching are nice.
This app is always freezing up. Not worth the money.
I like that it gives so much general advise about diet, exercise and focus,even without having to pay for the extra plans within the app.
Thanks to this app I am well on my way to fixing all my period problems...I've been using it for one cycle and will continue to use it without abandon :)
I have trouble getting it to open a lot but otherwise I love the information!
Can't add all of my symptoms. The free app I have with others works better. It gives good info but last time my cycle was 27 days and this time 30 days. It doesn't adjust with you. Please fix

I really like the recommendations the app gives you but what would make this successful is letting you track the start and end date of your period without messing up the entire cycle. I have had such a hard time getting it to adjust to my cycle that I just don't even bother using it anymore.
So interesting! I love finding out why I'm feeling the way I do and what might help.

When I first downloaded this app, I accidentally entered that my cycle was 38 days instead of 28. As a result, all of my recommendations were off. I contacted customer support who told me that it could not be changed. Seriously? Why did I pay money for this app? Even though I correctly entered the dates of my periods, the cycle recommendations did adjust. What a waste.

I downloaded this app when it was first released, but now 6+ months in I can honestly say it does not deliver on what it promised.  The premise of this app was to help you track your symptoms and period, to then actually get back to a normal 28 day cycle. The app doesn't deliver on this at all.  The symptoms that it asks for are too simplistic (and heavily geared towards the developer's overpriced programmes).  If you buy this app to try and get your cycle under control and find out where you are in your cycle, DO NOT BUY IT. When I started I had no idea when I would get my period (maybe once ever 6 weeks). Since then my periods have normalised, but the algorithm in the app has zero learning capability which means now I still am none the wiser when I am supposed to be getting my period, because the app still insists on having my cycle go for 6 weeks. Not good enough for a paid for app, that tries to dupe you into spending tonnes of money off the back of it.

I really like the recommendations based on my symptoms and the different phases. The part I find challenging is that I can't go back to add to or change symptoms/tracking if I forget to enter it before 12am the next day.
First day but I am happy there is something like this out there! Way to go FloLiving!

Disappointed as I loved this app at first, especially the recommendations. As an endo sufferer, trackibg my period has been hugely helpful. Have used free apps up to this point which lacked the suggestion aspect that My Flo gave. But after about three cycles I started having problems booking the period start date. App would crash and I'd be stuck with an inaccurate start date (wouldn't let me change as it kept crashing). Now it just crashes or throws a 'Not reaponding' message every time, rendering it completely useless. I've kept logging against WomanLog (the free app) all along so will just go back to that. Not great really considering My Flo is a paid app. Also, as others have said, it links your symptoms to different times in the cycle, so you can't have nausea at one point, it's as though the app thinks that's impossible (I wish!). If this is sorted out I kay go back. Hugely disappointing as this felt like a very positive step for me at the time.
I like that this app links your cycle to advice on food, exercise and what your hormones are doing. I find it lacking as far as charting for natural family planning goes.

So far, I love this! I do wish you could do more within the calendar, like track workouts and add notes. But I've learned so much more about what's happening within each phase of my cycle than I did before. I've paid for a lot of apps/books/resources in the past that have promised useful information on how to live, work and excersize around hormonal changes, but very few proved worthwhile. This app is definitely up there at the top of the "worth it" list!

I like being able to track my period and my symptoms  but wish there was a way I could look at the overall view of how many days / when I reported symptoms.  Don't like that after putting a sympton twice you are pushed to

Cool app
I deleted it. It didnt do more than my paper calendar. The suggestions, which were few, were common sense. I really had high hopes.
App is great. Works best if you have read her book Women Code to really understand the purpose of the app and the different cycles. :)
Great app. My only complaint is that it doesn't always work.  I guess that's a note for the tech dept.

I've only been using the app for 3 weeks but so far I love it.  It makes it easy to track your cycle and has a ton on useful information that is given to you in a timely manner according to where you are, not just dump truck of stuff all at once.  Would highly recommend to anyone who is looking to better understand what is going on with their body.

Best app I've ever bought! I have learned so so so much about my body..  My life is easier with this app.  I love the journal prompts and the way out tells me what to eat more of.  The app looks beautiful  as well so it's always a pleasure to look at and use.  I share And talk about this app whenever I get the chance.  Great work!
Offensive app! Make this app more family friendly / christian / wholesome by eliminating pics of immodestly dressed women, references to masturbation, prophylactics, and other offensive material.
Love the content, couldn't be more worth the purchase... But very glitchy. I restart it several times each time I use it... Yet I find the content worth all the effort.
Love this app! I've tried others, this one is way more informative and helpful.

I've been using this app for months and I just can't get into it. As others have said, symptoms list are predetermined for you, no way to add your own, you have to pay for more info, and app is still very buggy. At the moment, I can't even get past the loading screen. Thumbs down.

I loved it at first, but it is overall a poorly functioning app. You can't change period length after the initial setup. Hello, I'm trying to fix my period and that info is likely to change. Also, changing the start or end date of my period makes the app crazy and freeze up, doesn't change anything, loses data, etc. Really wanted to live this app because I really loved the book. But now I'm just frustrated that I paid for an app that doesn't work. Cannot recommend.
replyContent: Thank you for your feedback! I'm sorry that you are having issues with the app. We are working on changing the functionality of the app so that users are able to adjust their period length and add symptoms and notes that aren't currently available in the app. I hope once these changes have been implemented, you will be able to change your mind!

content: The app is useful for tracking hormonal changes throughout the month as well as providing tips on how to eat or exercise based on your time of month. There's quite a bit of information in this small app. One downside is that the app only gives a very short list of systems for each phase, but I have more symptoms that I'd like to track that aren't listed. Also, the app keeps prompting the user to purchase additional courses (of which I believe there are 8 options ranging from $50-$3000) in order to obtain more information. In general, it's a great idea and a useful tool, but still requires some work.  UPDATE: After only 3 months of using this app, I tried to change a period start date by only one day and it completely messed up the system. Nothing is on target anymore and I can't delete anything or start over. I'm super disappointed this app is so user-unfriendly. My advice: save your money until it works properly.
This app does not open consistently for me. Hard to keep track of my flo when the app doesn't work.

App rarely opens and is not personalized. The calendar is never accurate and also is a challenge to track symptoms because the options aren't always available to select. It has potential to be a great tool, but right now it is not worth it.
I've waited years for this app. I have lifestyle and diet suggestions to harness my hormonal super powers at my fingertips.  It sucks that a paid app is always trying to upsell, though...

I would like more symptom choices,  it's not as in depth as I was hoping and the prices for the meal plans they offer are ridiculous. On the plus side it's seems so far to track well and gives some insight into why I feel the way I do.
Horrible! It's a pain in the ass to load up and it deleted all the stuff I was keeping track of! The soul purpose of having the app was to keep track and compare!
I no longer have "surprise!" syptoms with my period cycleüòÜ I now have a way to work with my cycle instead of cursing it.

I love Floliving and Alisa Vitti's work! This app is a great start to opening up all this useful and sometimes life-changing information to the world. The calendar part of the app is hard to use though. I'd love to be able to manually put in when I ovulate especially.
Very cool app, my only complaint is lack of symptom choices during certain phases.

I love this app so far. Have had no experience of crashing or problem entering days. Yes it provides quite basic information but gives a strong starting point to do personal research and/or read the book alongside, which is brilliant (womancode)
Unable to scroll thru pop-up style windows... Which makes it difficult to see all the info or track all symptoms. Hope issues is resolved soon (also wouldn't let me report issue via app)
No reset button. Information generic and really user friendly

I love the recommendations based on my daily symptoms, and I feel as though to some degree they are helping as well. But the app isn't tracking my cycle properly-- says my avg. cycle is only 17 days and my last two have been closer to 35. Not adjusting properly. Also there are a lot of bugs with letting the app know when your period starts and ends, and the help/feedback request page doesn't work at all.

I thought this app would have a lot more functionality and personalisation. There are a lot of improvements that can be made. E.g. being able to see an overview of own symptoms to understand patterns rather than just a list of dates. Would be great to add own symptoms too. Also, don't understand why the FloRX programs are SO expensive for a bunch of emails and reminders. Really inhibitive pricing for the average person. For ¬£200 you can go and see a Harley Street doctor face-to-face!

when i first got this app I absolutely loved it, I loved that it told you how to address your symptoms. But after using it for 4 cycles I realized it just gave me the same information over and over. The cycle calendar is really confusing and there are a lot of bugs about recording the start and stop of your period. Definitely won't be using it anymore until they improve the interface, add more symptom options, and fix the bugs.

I love that the app is interactive and truly helpful by suggesting food and lifestyle fixes for any symptoms. The only thing that is a little frustrating is the 'my period started' button doesn't go away and I keep seeing a reminder that I am late even though I touch the 'undo' and it indicates that my period started 2 days ago. Because of that then I don't have the option to select the end date of my period :/ I truly believe this is the best app for balancing hormones though! :)

Can't track all the symptoms as it automatically assumes eg that your period finished so you cannot possibly feel nausea or fatigue.  Also cannot change end of your period manually! ! !  So one of my cycles was longer but cannot change it. It assumes my period is 4 days and that's it. No flexibility.  It's extremely disappointing as I loved the book and couldn't wait to get the adroit app.   I expected so much more.

I think this app is good for people who have no clue what their cycles are or how to avoid symptoms. Beyond that though, it doesn't really get to know you after logging for s while like other tracking apps. Also, it's been super buggy. I used to hsve an iPhone and it worked fine, but on my new samsung I can rarely get it to open fully. Most of the time I don't bother tracking each day because I forget to go back to the app and see if it'll open after the first time it doesnt. This wouldn't even be ok for a free app. It seriously needs to be addressed becsuse it looks like I'm not the only one with this issue
Save yourself the $!
Love all the tips and advice
Good info but it keeps crashing

It isn't personalized at all unless you start paying for expensive programs. What a disappointment. I am tired of this "always be selling" woman and her VERY HIDDEN value add. I purchased this app in good faith and now I am mad. Guess I will be doing my own research, I am not so desperate as to pay $47 for a set of emails about nutrition around my period. Any standard period tracker is better than this nonsense.

Pissed off I paid for this and would really like a refund. Doesn't track my cycles at all. Even after inputting three full regular cycles on the calendar, it still says my next cycle is 7 months away. Complete waste of money.
The beginning of living again

Doesnt track correctly after months of use and continues to be buggy. Only works glad the time. I don't recommend this app for period teaching. There are better (free) apps out there. Save your money.
Lots of bugs. I updated the app and rebooted the phone but the calendar goes nuts which makes it useless. As an alumni of Alissa's work for more than 5 years, I was expecting more from a paid app.

Really enjoyed the extra info about each stage of the cycle and suggestions for food/lifestyle for each stage that sets this apart from other apps I've used. Looking forward to updates (hoping for more options/flexibility with updating cycle length and symptoms and a place for notes).
Helps me remember to pay attention to these hormonal signs.

So far so good. I've had the app for about 3 weeks and I've not had any issues with loading. The information provided is helpful and practical. I am looking forward to the next installment with even more features and options, particularly the symptom tracking.

This app is so helpful!! Especially if you're looking to do pregnancy planning. It's interesting to read about what's going on with your body and mind. It helps you to embrace your monthly cycle rather than hate on it! Love this app
Useful info. But technical issues like not opening, then crashing.
Love this app... Would be great if the lunar phases were also included in the app :)

Tracking incorrectly. First said cycle every 42 days, now has me at every 12; both are incorrect. Uninstalled/reinstalled once already. And I can't send feedback because it won't send it! Currently feels like a waste of money.

**update.. the app no longer works. My cycle isn't perfect so I clicked to indicate a day early and the app had a meltdown. Won't open so all the data I had been logging to share with my doctor to request blood work is lost. I've found no way to contact for help, no reply on social media and I can't open the app for the built in help portal.  Great start but this app is missing things for me. A place to track bmt, even if it's not being considered for advice to improve cycles. Some of just want to be healthy, not pregnant, know ovulation is important when you're encouraging allowing the body to regulate without birth control pills/iud. No way to pull the data from the app, this is good info to discuss with a medical professional that is willing to help improve reproductive health.  Also, there are a lot of sales opportunities which is disappointing. Having heavy cramps? Here are a few tips and for 49.95 try program x to really get it right. This was advertised as a companion to the book, why isn't there a reference to where in the book we can read more about it so if/when we spend on a program it's going to be because we really need the guidance. There is something empowering of being able to improve your own wellness, of having the tools and knowing how to use them

It's helpful in allowing you to track your period and helps you to become aware of symptoms and gives advice to help manage these symptoms but if you want any more than that you have to pay for the specific programmes. Considering I paid for this app I expected a lot more from it. I ended up using it for one month and then giving up because the information it gives is so basic and impersonal it's pointless.
This app has been invaluable to managing my cycle. It's even been a relationship saver.
Such a great help in maximizing my cycle!

I purchased and installed this app on my phone three weeks ago. Managed to use it for less than a week. Now when i try to open it nothing happens.the  furthest it goes is the purple screen.ive updated the app..rebooted my phone. Still nothing! I'm quite upset about it because I  payed for it. Money down the drain!

The app (that I paid for) crashed an hour after purchasing it, worked for about 2 weeks and now it won't even open. Even when it did work I somehow indicated my period had started when it hadn't (and couldn't change it) so any of the great advice being offered didn't even apply. I'm really disappointed because I have been following Alisa's work for some time and expected at least a functioning app especially considering I was charged money for this.
This app gets you in tune with your femaleness with food recommendations, hormonal effects on your mood and much more. Get ready to feel like a woman and get in the Flo!
Brilliant way to track your monthly cycle, every woman can benefit even if they don't suffer from any hormonal imbalances or issues with their periods.

I love this app. It's helped me track my cycle and get my hormones back in order and control my PCOS. I just went through my first cycle without being bed ridden for day from PMS and chronic pain. Definately recommend it to anyone trying to take back control of their FLO.

I like this app. Very useful. I'm not a fan of tracking exercise,ect. But something about having tips on eating and exercise that is more specific to my body on that day helps keep my movement and eating practices on track.

I love this app!! It's like having Alissa personally advise me on my hormonal journey each month. I love the immediate daily suggestions...foods to fix problems, what projects to focus on, how to exercise & when to take it easy.

I love it! The information is excellent and the interface is lovely. I just wish I could put in that I gave birth and am breastfeeding, it's not an essential tweak so you still get 5 stars - thank you!

I found Alisa about a month ago when I was recently diagnosed with PCOS and was looking for treatments other than the pill. She is amazing, I love her food and lifestyle tips. And now that the app is released, I can't be more grateful to get the tips reminded to me daily. Love Alisa and her amazing Floliving team!! :)

Overall, the app is great! One thing that would make it a 5 is adding specific recipes for each week and more information on what can be incorporated to prevent and/or eliminate the conditions specifically.
So far so good! I'm excited to see how the app continues to inform me as I use it consistently, but the cycle-specific lifestyle and workout tips wrapped into the daily info are hugely helpful.

Love the principles of this app. Great idea. And I love all the advice. I wish it wasn't so expensive. I understand why it is but... I'm not feelin it. Anyway I love the rest of it! Sometimes the app does crash though. That needs to be worked on.
Never before done!! Unique and helpful, a must have for all women.

I must say I am rather disappointed.  I was expecting more content. When it says I get a customised 4 week functional nutrition protocol I expect that to be part of the app price and not cost 49$+. Otherwise there is some interesting information, however it is lacking included information on how to fix the symptoms she says are not normal.
Glad Alissa's app is here!! Loving it.
So excited to finally have this app! Great that it's a tracker that actually helps you DO something with that information. And Alisa's work is amazing!
Yay! I'm reading the WomanCode book right now & I'm so excited about this app! Marvelous! Love Alisa's genuine, sweet & humorous personality! Xoxox

I freaking love it. I love it! I struggle with PCOS and a lot of its worst symptoms. I must have read WomanCode 8 times. I was able to get pregnant naturally twice with this lifestyle, and now I just need hormonal stability without having to thumb through the book all the time. This app provides that!

been waiting for this app to come out for a while on android.  Its really cool, but a bit disappointed that it doesn't say the complete list of foods to eat for each cycle with recipes for that cycle like in the book... that would be a great upgrade.
